The divorce process in South Africa is relatively straightforward. The first step is to file a divorce petition with the court. This is usually done by the husband, but can also be done by the wife. The petition will include details of the marriage, the reasons for the divorce, and any other relevant information.

The next step is to serve the petition on the other party. This is usually done by a sheriff or constable, but can also be done by a private investigator. The petition will include details of the marriage, the reasons for the divorce, and any other relevant information.
